Package: fdrID
Type: Package
Title: Computes local false discovery rate probabilities using JAGS, Stan and code from Efron, Turnbull and Narasimhan locfdr
Version: 1.0
Date: 2015-05-25
Author: Nick Petraco
Maintainer: <npetraco@gmail.com>
Description: Using ideas from Ann. Stat. 35(4):1351-1377 (2007), and some handy code from the former locfdr package, this package computes local false discovery rate (i.e. posterior error probability) estimates for classification/discrimination tasks using a Bayesian Poission regression. Specifically, the Bayesian Poission regression is used to estimate the denominator of Bayes Theorem within Efron's two-groups empirical Bayes methodology. The regression is a heirarical model and carried out with either JAGS (mcmc-jags.sourceforge.net) or Stan (mc-stan.org), via their R interfaces.
SystemRequirements: JAGS (http://mcmc-jags.sourceforge.net), Stan (mc-stan.org), rstan (https://github.com/stan-dev/rstan/wiki/RStan-Getting-Started)
License: GPL (>= 2)
Imports: R2jags (>= 0.5-6), rstan (>= 2.6.0), fBasics (>= 3011.87), nortest (>= 1.0-3) 
Depends: R2jags (>= 0.5-6), rstan (>= 2.6.0), fBasics (>= 3011.87), nortest (>= 1.0-3)